headline: Has Walmart’s 2025 Surge and Online Expansion Already Been Fully Reflected in Its Price?
summary: Wondering if Walmart at $115.66 is still a smart buy after such a strong run, or if most of the upside is already priced in? You are not alone. That is exactly what this breakdown aims to unpack. Over the short term, the stock is up 2.2% over the last week and 12.3% over the past month, building on a hefty 28.5% year to date gain and a striking 147.9% and 159.3% over the last 3 and 5 years respectively.
